 :tx/rationale "SOLUTION ARCHITECTURE: Three mechanisms at three time scales. (1) IMMEDIATE (during observe): When braid observe text contains actionable verbs (implement, add, create, fix, wire, build, refactor, test) AND references a system component (file path, spec ID, module name), append a SUGGESTION to the guidance footer: 'Actionable decision detected. Crystallize: braid task create <auto-title> --relates-to <obs-entity>'. The auto-title is extracted from the observation using the same NLP that extract_task_files uses for file paths. This is the PREVENTION layer — the prompt nudges the agent to create the task in the same cognitive flow. (2) HARVEST-TIME (end of session): harvest_pipeline already scans for harvestable knowledge. Add a new harvest check: for each observation with :intent/decision category or actionable verb content, query for tasks that reference the observation entity OR tasks with similar title text. If no match, include in harvest report as 'UNTRACKED DECISIONS: N decisions reference implementation work with no corresponding task'. This is the DETECTION layer. (3) SEED-TIME (start of next session): When braid seed assembles context for the next session, include untracked decisions PROMINENTLY in the Next Actions section: 'From prior session: 3 design decisions without tasks. Crystallize first: (1) braid task create ... (2) braid task create ...' This carries the orphaned decisions ACROSS sessions — the next agent sees them immediately. This is the CORRECTION layer — the system LEARNS about untracked decisions and surfaces them proactively."
